title: Tract on astrology and magic : manuscript.

notes.text: Incipit (folio 1b): "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Ahkam sabah lil-saah wa-sharaituha wa-sifatuha sifat al-shams. Wa-bi-hi nastain. Fasl fi marifat kitab al-saah al-khabar wa-huwa al-sabah al-sami li-ayyam al-sabah wa-ma yakhtassu bihima. Qala Allah taala: Wa-Huwa alladhi jaala lakum al-nujuma li-tahtadu biha fi zulumati al-barri wa-al-bahri. Wa-huwa kawkab allati fi ayyam al-sabah. Wa-ilam waffaqaka Allah taala wa-arshadaka al-taqwa bi-anna al-saah al-awwal min yawm al-Ahad li-saat al-shams, wa-huwa tatlau fi falak al-rabi wa-yuqimu fi buruj shahr ..."
Script: In fair naskh script; in black ink, on cream color paper; catchwords.
Binding: Unbound; the codex is placed inside a folded sheet of parchment.
Colophon: "Kataba Ali ibn Habib (?) ibn Ali ibn Midhat (?) ghafar Allah al-dhunubahu."

title: Navigation : prepared expressly for the use of the midn. at the U.S. Naval Academy : manuscript / by William Chauvenet, A.M.

notes.text: Onwership inscription to first free endpaper: Midn. Lewis Clark, U.S.N.
Front cover and title page loose.
Examination address caption title: An address, delivered at the annual examination of the United States Naval Academy by Hon. Edward Everett, 28th May, 1863.

title: Estate records of the Fairholme / Pringle family of Greenknowe, Berwickshire, Scottish Borders : manuscript.

notes.text: This material is available for research.
Title devised by cataloger, based on dealer's description.

title: Yndice de las r[eale]s cedulas que contiene este legajo o. quaderno 4o que corre desde el ano de 1713 : manuscript.

notes.text: Size of original binding indicates that original manuscript also contained the texts of the volume.
Manuscript is written in two diferent hands. Second hand starts with decree number 144, dated to May 1751.
Manuscript annotation in a different hand emphasizing decree number 60: Sobre las confirmaciones de oficios dada en Seuilla a 6. de Agosto de 1732.
It is unclear whether the manuscript was written in Spain or Latin America.

title: Alfred Stieglitz letter, to Arthur Dove : with attached photograph by Stieglitz : manuscript.

notes.text: Place and date from similar photograph in the collection of the National Gallery of Art.

title: 880-02 Shifa al-haim fi sharh bad al-Daaim : manuscript / Abu al-Qasim ibn Ibrahim al-Barradi.

notes.text: Name of copyist and place and date of copying not mentioned, probably from the 18th century.

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Allahumma yassir alayna. al-Hamdu lillah fatir al-sabiayn al-sama wa-al-ard, al-mujid al-mujadayn al-jism wa-al-ard, alladhi jaala al-khalq mutadawalan bayna al-ifna wa-al-ijad, muwahhidan bayna alam al-islah wa-alam al-ifsad [crossed over] al-fasad, wa-khassa al-alam al-mukallaf bi-al-ishqa wa-al-isad, wa-jaala al-ilm afdal wa-afkhar al-makasib ..."
Script: In large clear naskh script; in black ink, on white paper; the verses of the poem "al-Daaim"; few notes and corrections on the margins; catchwords.
Binding: In dark brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.
Inside the front cover and folio 1a-1b: Miscellaneous quotations in different hands.

On folio 2a: "Kitab al-Haim, Shifa al-haim fi sharh bad al-Daaim, talif al-Shaykh al-Imam al-alim al-allamah Abi al-Qasim ibn Ibrahim al-Barradi al-Maghribi al-Nafusi, rahimahu Allah taala wa-ghafara la-hu wa-li-jami al-muminin wa-al-muminat, al-ahya minhum wa-al-amwat, innahu huwa al-ghafur al-rahim. Katabahu al-faqir al-haqir Abd Allah ibn Muhammad ibn Amir ibn Muhammad ibn Hubaysh(?) al-Samadi al-Nazwi."
On folio 2a: A statement dated 9 Safar 1243 of the Hijrah (1 September 1827), as follows: "Tarikh wusulina al-Yaman yawm 9 Safar, sanat 1243".
Title from folio 5a: "... wa-sammaytuhu 'Shifa al-haim fi sharh bad al-Daaim' ..."

Colophon: No colophon. Text ends with a long poem on ritual purity "Wa-qala fi al-wudu wa-al-tayammum wa-ghasl al-najasat wa-al-ightisal wa-al-janabah wa-ahkam al-taharat": "... Kaannama al-satru idha shumtahu // yusirru bi-al-dihki ila al-satri. Ka-iqdi ghayda ala nahriha // mufassalun bi-al-durri wa-al-shadhri. Tammat."

title: 880-02 al-Nahw wa-tafsir shay min al-Quran : manuscript / Ahmad ibn Muhammad al-Haddadi.

notes.text: Name of copyist and place and date of copying not mentioned, probably from the 18th century.

Incipit: "Kitab al-Haddadi. Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Qala al-faqih al-Imam al-mufassir al-zahid Abu Nasr Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn Rashdan (?) ibn Muhammad al-Haddadi: Lamma faraghtu min tasnif kitabi al-Mudih li-ilm al-Quran sannaftu kitabi hadha minni li-waladi wa-li-sair al-Muslimin wa-jaaltuhu madkhalan li-tafsir Kitab Allah wa-maanihi, wa-tanbihan ala turuqihi wa-mabanihi, wa-raddan ala al-mulhidin wa-al-tainin fi Kitab Allah ..."
Layout: In one column of 18 lines.
Script: In fair naskh script; in black ink, on white paper; some wormholes without loss of text; catchwords.
Binding: In dark brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.
Includes a table of contents on folios 5a-7a.
Folio 141 is a duplicate of folio 11, written in the same hand.
Decoration: Headings and markings in red.

Colophon (flolio 137a): "Tamma Kitab 'al-Nahw wa-tafsir shay min al-Quran', bi-awn al-Malik al-Mannan. Nasalu Allah al-salamah min al-isyan wa-al-najah min al-niran, innahu karimun mannan, rahimun rahman, wa-la hawla wa-la quwata illa billah al-Ali al-azim."

title: 880-03 Diwan al-sababah : manuscript / Ahmad ibn Yahya ibn Abi Hajalah.

notes.text: Copied on Tuesday evening, five days remaining from the month of Safar, of the year 1123 of the Hijrah (14 April 1711), by Sulayman ibn Rabi (?) ibn Harmal (?) ibn Hamad al-Amiri, for his patron, Sultan ibn al-Imam Sayf ibn Sultan ibn Sayf ibn Malik al-Yarubi. Place of copying not mentioned.

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim, wa-bi-hi nastain. Rabbi Yassir. al-Hamdu lillah alladhi jaala lil-ashiqin bi-ahkam al-gharam ridan, wa-habbaba ilayhim al-mawt fi hubb man yahwawnahu, fa-la takun ya fata bi-al-adhli mutaridan, fa-kam fihim min ashiqin wa-muhibbin sadiq. Shiran: Raa fa-habba fa-rama al-wasla fa-imtanau // fa-sama sabran fa-aya nayluhu fa-qada ..."
Layout: In single column of 14 lines.
Script: In fair naskh script; in black ink, on white paper; some wormholes without loss of text; catchwords.
Binding: In dark brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.

On folio 1a: "Hadha Kitab Diwan al-sababah, li-malikihi al-faqir lillah azza wa-jall, Sultan ibn al-Imam Sayf ibn Sultan ibn Sayf ibn Malik al-Yarubi. Katabahu malikuhu bi-yadihi." Under it: "Hadha al-kitab li-malikihi, Imam al-Muslimin, Sultan ibn Sayf ibn Sultan ibn Sayf ibn Malik al-Yarubi. Katabahu malikuhu bi-yadihi. Tarikh kitabi hadha yawm al-Ithnayn, arbaah wa-ishrin Rabi al-Akhir, sanat 1127 min al-Hijrah al-Nabawiyah [29 April 1715]."
On Folio 1a: A partially legible ownership statement: "Intaqala hadha al-kitab bi-al-shira al-sahih min Suq al-Rustaq [obliterated words]."
On folios 2a-3b: Miscellaneous quotations in poetry and prose.

On folio 4a: "Hadha Kitab 'Diwan al-sababah', talif al-Shaykh al-Imam al-fadil, al-adib al-allamah, Shihab al-Din Abi al-Abbas Ahmad ibn Abi Hajalah al-Tilimsani, lil-Sayyid al-Mawla al-muazzam Sultan ibn Imam al-Muslimin Sayf ibn Sultan ibn Sayf al-Yarubi, khallada Allah mulkahum. Katabahu abduhu Salman ibn Sayf ibn Salman bi-yadihi."
On folio 209b: Several ownership statements. And a reader's statement dated 7 Rabi al-Akhir, sanat 1257 (29 May 1841)
Decooration: Headings and markings in red.

Colophon (flolio 208a-208b): "Huna intaha akhir 'Diwan al-sababah' li-Ibn Abi Hajalah, wa-nuqila min nuskhatin bi-khatt al-Shaykh al-adib al-fadil Muhammad ibn Ibrahim ibn Muhammad ibn Ibrahim al-Shadhili, al-shahir al-maruf bi-al-Badr al-Sinani (?). Tamma al-kitab bi-awn al-Malik al-Wahhab, ashiyat al-thulatha, li-khamsin baqyat min Safar, sanat thalath wa-ishrin wa-miah wa-alf <sanah> min Hijrat al-Nabi Muhammad [14 April 1711], Salla Allah alayhi wa-alihi, wa-sallam, ala yaday al-faqir ila Allah taala, Sulayman ibn Rabi (?) ibn Harmal (?) ibn Hamad al-Amiri, nasakhahu li-makhdumihi wa-sayyidihi wa-muli yadihi wa-rabbi nimatihi wa-kashif ghummatihi, Sultan ibn al-Imam Sayf ibn Sultan ibn Sayf ibn Malik al-Yarubi, atala Allah amarahuma, wa-adama izzahuma, wa-manaa al-khutub an tabuzzahuma, innahu jawwadun karim. Wa-la hawla wa-la quwata illa billah al-Ali al-Azim. Tamm. Tamm. Tamm." Around the colophon (in red): "Tamma. Tamma. Tamma. Wa-kana tahbiruhu ala yaday abdihi, wa-asir judihi, wa-arif ihsanihi, al-shakir fadlahu, Sulayman ibn Sayf ibn Sulayman ibn Bashir al-Mighfari (?) [one word torn]. Wa-kana al-faragh min dhalika yawm 10 Rabi al-Awwal, sanat 1123 [18 April 1711]."

title: 880-03 Qasidat al-Burdah : manuscript / Sharaf al-Din Muhammad ibn Said al-Busiri.

notes.text: Name of copyist and place and date of copying not mentioned, probably from the 18th century.

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Qala al-Shaykh al-Imam al-alim al-allamah, fakhr al-udaba, jamal al-bulagha, Sharaf al-Din Abu Abd Allah Muhammad ibn Said al-Dulasi thumma al-Busiri, rahmat Allah alayhi: Kana sabab inshai hadhihi al-qasidah al-mubarakah anni kuntu qad asabani khalit falij abtala nisfi wa-lam antafi bi-hi, fa-fakkartu an amala qasidatan fi madh al-Nabi, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam, astashfiu bi-hi ila Allah, azza wa-jall, fa-anshatu hadhihi al-qasidah, wa-numtu, fa-rayatu al-Nabi, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam, fi al-manam, fa-masaha alayya bi-yadihi al-mubarakah, fa-ufitu li-waqti ..."
Script: In good naskh script; in black ink, on cream color paper; text fully vocalized; catchwords.
Decoration: Interlinear translation in Ottoman Turkish (in red).
At the head of folio 1a (in a different hand): "Qasidat Burdah".
Colophon (flolio 14b): "Tammat Qasidat al-Burdah biawn Allah taala wa-husn tawfiqihi, wa-salla Allah ala Sayyidina Muhammad wa-alihi wa-sahbihi ajamin."

title: 880-02 Muwassil al-tullab ila Qawaid al-irab : manuscript / Khalid ibn Abd Allah al-Azhari.

notes.text: Incipit: The beginning is missing. Text starts as follows: "... alayhi wa-inna al-jumlah aamm min al-kalam, fa-kull kalam jumlah wa-la yanakis, ala tara anna nahwa jumlat In qama Zaydun fi qawlika In qama Zaydun qama Amr, wa-summiya jumlatan wa-la yusmma kalaman li-annahu la yahsunu al-sukut alayhi, thumma inna al-jumlah tusamma ismiyah in budiat bi-ism ..."
Script: In ornate naskh script; in black ink, on thick cream color and greenish paper; with marginal and notes; two inserts of commentaries; catchwords.
Decoration: Titles and markings in red.

Colophon (flolio 15b): "Wa-fi hadha al-qadr fi hadha al-mukhtasar kifayah li-mutaammilihi. Lillah al-hamd wa-al-minnah. Bi-ismihi, subhanuhu wa-taala, faragha min kitabatihi al-abd al-muftaqir Ali fi yawm al-Jumah [crossed over] al-Sabt, fi waqt al-zuhr, fi Qaryat Jizki (?). al-Hamdu lillah Rabb al-Alamin hamdan yuwafi niamah wa-yukafi mazidah, wa-salla Allah taala ala Rasulihi Muhammad, wa-ala alihi wa-ashabihi jamian. Amin. Ya Muin."

title: 880-02 Khizanat al-akhyar fi sharh buyuat al-khiyar : manuscript / Khamis ibn Said ibn Ali.

notes.text: Copied by Abd Allah ibn Mubarak ibn Umar ibn Hilal ibn Abd Allah, who was in the service of the Umani ruler Nasir ibn Murshid al-Yarubi (Muayyad al-Yarubi, Nasir ibn Murshid, active 17th century).

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Rabbi yassir, Ya Karim. Mimma anshaahu al-Alim al-allamah, wahid dahrihi wa-nasij wahdihi, Qadi al-Muslimin Khamis ibn Said ibn Ali, rahimahu Allah. al-Hamdu lillah alladhi antaqa bi-al-hikamah alsun al-ulama al-arifin, wa-jala ghishawat al-shakk an absar basair al-uqala al-khaifin, wa-kashafa hujub al-yaqin an ayun qulub al-awliya al-muhtadin ... wa-sammaynahu bi-kitab 'Khizanat al-akhyar fi sharh buyuat al-khiyar' ..."
Script: In fair naskh script; in black ink, on white paper; catchwords.
Binding: In brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.

Colophon: "Tamma al-kitab al-mubarak al-musamma bi-Khizanat al-akhyar fi buyuat al-khiyar, bi-awn al-Malik al-jabbar al-aziz al-ghaffar, wa-kana sadara hadha al-kitab bi-khatt malikihi al-Alim al-amil ... Khamis ibn Said ibn Ali ... wa-kana dhalika fi sab wa- [... ... ...] min al-Hijrah al-Nabawiyah ... wa-kana tamamuhu min nuskhah bi-khatt muallifihi al-Faqih Abd Allah ibn Muhammad ibn Ghassan ibn Muhammad (?) ... Katabahu al-faqir lillah al-Ghani Abd Allah ibn Mubarak ibn Umar ibn Hilal ibn Abd Allah al-Murtaji (?) ... wa-kana yawmidhin fi khidmat al-Malik ... Nasir ibn Murshid ibn Malik ... al-Yarubi, amaddahu Allah taala bi-suud ayyamih ... bi-hurmat Sayyid al-Mursalin wa-al-Ruh al-Amin, salla Allah alayhima, wa-ala alihi ajmain."

title: 880-02 Hall al-Mujiz : manuscript / Muhammad ibn Muhammad al-Aqsarai.

notes.text: Copied on Monday 18 Dhu al-Qadah of the year 1126 of the Hijrah (25 November 1714). Name of copyist, etc. obliterated.

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. al-Hamdu lillah Rabb al-Alamin, wa-al-salah wa-al-salam ala afdal anbiyaihi Muhammad wa-alihi ajmain. Wa-bad, <fa-inna talab> fa-inna al-tibb ilmun sharif li-sharaf mawduihi wa-wathaqat dalailihi, wa-shiddat al-hajah ilayhi, wa-fi al-ishtighal bi-hi min al-thawab al-jazil ma la yusafu, li-tadammunihi izhar athar rahmat Allah taala ala ibadihi, wa-al-tawassul bi-hi ila irahat nufusihim an al-asqam, fa-li-dhalika saraftu bad zaman tahsili ilayhi, wa-qaratu al-mukhtasarat al-mashhurah fihi ala walidi ... wa-sammaytuhu bi-Hall al-Mujiz, li-annahu yahullu ma fihi min al-mushkilat wa-al-mulghazat, wa-ma tawfiqi illa billah, alayhi tawakkaltu wa-ilayhi unib ..."
Script: In good naskh script; in black ink, on polished white paper; catchwords.
Binding: In brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.

Colophon: "Tammat kitabat hadha al-kitab bi-awn al-Malik al-Wahhab, al-shafi lima asab, wa-huwa al-musamma bi-Sharh al-Aqsarai, yawm al-Ithnayn, wa 18 min al-Qadah, sanat 1126 [25 November 1714], bi-qalam al-faqir ila Allah taala, al-mudhnib [the rest of the colophon obliterated]."
Script: In splendid calligraphic naskh script; in black ink, on cream color paper; badly water-stained; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings in gold, red, and blue; text within line border of gold and blue; unwans in gold and colors at the beginning; gilt floral decorations in the margins.
Binding: In dark brown leather, Type III (without flap); cover inside colored cloth jacket.

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Salla Allah ala Sayyidina wa-Mawlana Muhammad, wa-ala alihi wa-sahbihi wa-sallam. al-Hamdu lillah alladhi hadana lil-iman wa-al-Islam, wa-al-salah ala Nabiyihi Muhammad alladhi istanqadhana bi-hi min ibadat al-awthan wa-al-asnam, wa-ala alihi wa-sahbihi wa-sallam, wa-ashabihi al-nujaba al-bararah al-kiram. Wa-bada hadha, fa-al-gharad min hadha al-kitab dhikr al-salah ala al-Nabi, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam wa-fadailiha, nadhkuruha mahfudhat al-asanid li-yashula hifzuha ala al-qari ..."
Script: In primitive naskh script; in black ink, on white European paper; catchwords.
Binding: The loose three quires of which some leaves seem to be missing are placed inside a folded deteriorated sheet of dark brown leather.

Colophon: No colophon. Text ends abruptly, as follows: "... Allahumma salli ala Sayyidina wa-Mawlana Muhammad rida nafsika. Allahumma salli ala Sayyidina wa-Mawlana Muhammad midada kalimatika. Allahumma salli ala Sayyidina wa-Mawlana Muhammad mila samawatika wa-ardika. Allahumma salli ala Sayyidina wa-Mawlana Muhammad zinata arshika. Allahumma salli ala Sayyidina wa-Mawlana Muhammad adada makhluqatika. Allahumma salli ..."

title: 880-03 Lawami al-asrar fi Sharh Matali al-anwar : manuscript / Muhammad ibn Muhammad al-Qutb al-Tahtani.

notes.text: Copied on 12 Shaban of the year 1108 of the Hijrah (6 March 1697), by Yaqub ibn Muhammad ibn Hidayah al-Qazwini (?) al-Awali. Place of copying not mentioned.
Title from folio 3a "... wa-sammaytuha bi-'Lawami al-asrar fi Sharh Matali al-anwar' ..."

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim, wa-bi-hi thiqati. al-Hamdu lillah fayyad dhawarif al-awarif wa-mulhim haqaiq al-maarif, wahib hayat al-alimin wa-rafi darajat al-alimin [al-amilin (?)], wa-al-salah ala khayr bariyatihi fi khaliqatihi, Muhammad, wa-alihi khayr al, ma zahara lami al wa-khatara manan bi-bal. Wa-bad, fa-inna al-ulum ala tashaub fununiha wa-takaththur shujuniha arfa al-matalib wa-anfa al-maarib, wa-ilm al-mantiq min bayniha abyanuha tibyanan wa-ahsanuha shanan ..."
Script: In medium clear naskh script; in black ink, on white polished paper; few notes and corrections on the margins; catchwords.
Decoration: The phrases of "Matali al-anwar" in red.
Binding: In brownish red leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.

Colophon: "Wafaqa al-faragh min taswid hadhihi al-sutur min hadha al-kitab al-mawsum bi-al-Matali, li-khulasat al-ikhwan, al-Shaykh al-taqi al-naqi, wa-al-radi al-murdi, al-Shaykh Yusuf ibn al-Shaykh Ali ibn Jafar al-Barburi al-Awali, ala yad aqall al-ibad amalan wa-aktharihim zalalan, ghariq bahr al-khataya wa-al-dhunub, Yaqub ibn Muhammad ibn Hidayah al-Qazwini (?) al-Awali, tahriran bi-al-yawm al-thani ashar min shahr Shaban, khutima bi-al-khayr wa-al-rudwan, ahad shuhur sanat al-thaminah wa-al-miah bada al-alf Hijriyah Nabawiyah [6 March 1697], ala muhajiriha afdal al-salah wa-al-salam."

title: 880-03 Dalail al-khayrat wa-shawariq al-anwar fi dhikr al-salah ala al-Nabi al-Mukhtar : manuscript / Muhammad ibn Sulayman al-Jazuli.

notes.text: Copied on Saturday, 12 Dhu al-Qadah, of the year 1151 of the Hijrah (21 February 1739). Place of copying not mentioned.
Title from folio 2a "... wa-sammaytuhu bi-Kitab 'Dalail al-khayrat wa-shawariq al-anwar fi dhikr al-salah ala al-Nabi al-Mukhtar' ..."

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Wa-salla Allah ala Sayyidina Muhammad, wa-ala alihi wa-sahbihi wa-sallam. Qala al-Shaykh al-Faqih Abu Abd Allah Muhammad ibn Sulayman al-Jazuli, rahimahu Allah wa-nafaana bi-hi wa-bi-amthalihi. Amin. al-Hamdu lillah alladhi hadana lil-iman wa-al-Islam, wa-al-salah wa-al-salam ala Muhammad Nabiyihi alladhi intaqadhna bi-hi min ibadat al-awthan wa-al-asnam, wa-ala alihi al-nujaba al-bararah al-kiram. Wa-bada hadha, fa-al-gharad fi hadha al-kitab dhikra [al-salah] ala al-Nabi, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam, wa-fadailuha, nadhkuruha mahdhufat al-asanid, li-yashula hifzuha ala al-qari ..."
At the head of folio 1b (in a different hand): "Audhu billah min al-Shaytan al-Rajim. Ya Fattah iftah lana, abwabaka. Nasrun min Allah wa-fathun qarib."
Script: In fairly good naskh script; in black ink, on thick cream color paper; some notes and corrections on the margins; text fully vocalized; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and keywords in red; colored drawings on folio 12b and 13a.
Binding: In brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with gilded central medallion and geometric design.
Text ends on folio 80b. Followed by miscellaneous prayers and invocations (folios 81b-92b) in different hands.

Colophon: "Wa-wafaqa al-faragh min naskh hadha al-Dalayil yawm al-Sabt al-mubarak, ithnay ashar fi shahr Dhi al-Qadah sanat alf wa-miah wahid wa-khamsin [21 February 1739]. Tamm. Faraghtu minha hamidan musalliyan musalliman Ya Rabbu fa-irham man ala katibihi tarahhuman." Araound the colophon: "Aya qaria khatti saaltuka dawatan ila Allahi lil-abdi al-musii bi-filihi li-yaghfira Allahu li dhanbi wa-yamhu khatiyati wa-yarziqani rizqan mughnian (?)."

title: Treatise on "Nifas" and "Hayd" according to Islamic law : manuscript.

notes.text: Incipit of Section 1. The beginning is missing. Text starts with: "... al-nifas laysa la-hu aqall. Wa-qala wa-qad rufia ilayna fi al-Hadith anna al-Nabi, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam, annahu qala 'La nifas aqall min usbuayn'. Wa-law lam nalam hadha al-Hadith an al-Nabi, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam, sahihan la akhadhna bi-hi. Wa-qala wa-qad rufia ilayna an Abi Mansur annahu qala aqall al-nifas ma tahurat alayhi fi awwal walad waladathu. Wa-Allah alam ..."

Incipit of Section 2: "Masalah manqulah min khatt al-Shaykh al-Alim al-Allamah Salih ibn Waddah, rahimahu Allah. Wa-amma al-amah idha hadat haydatan wa-inqataa anha al-dam fa-jaizun tazwijuha wa-tasarriha, li-annahu qala bad al-Muslimin al-istibra bi-haydah. Wa-Allah alam. Wa-huwa qawlun min aqwal al-Muslimin, wa-qawl hatta tahida haydatayn. Wa-man akhadha bi-al-qawl al-awwal lam naqul innahu rakab (?) majar (?). Ma katabahu Salih ibn Waddah bi-yadihi naqaltuhu kama wajadtuhu ..."

Incipit of Section 3 (Preceded by a table of contents): "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Bab fi sifat al-hayd wa-dam al-istihadah. Qala Abu al-Muddaththir: Dam al-hayd damun ghaliz aswad asyas la yakadu yakhruju min al-thawb idha ghusila. Wa-qad dhukira lana anna Aishah, radiya Allah anha, kanat idha ightasalat fa-baqiya la-hu athar fa-ghayyarathu bi-shay min sufrah. Wa-dam al-istihadah damun raqiq ahmar. Hadha nahfaz. Wa-Allah alam ..."
Script: In fair naskh script; in black ink, on thick cream color paper; few notes on the margins; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and keywords in red.
Binding: In dark brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.

On pleminary leaf 2b: An ownership statement: "Milk hadha al-kitab intaqala li-Sayyidina Salim ibn Sultan, ishtarahu min Bandar, tarikh yawm 12 Shawwal, sanat 1226 [30 October 1811], wa-katabahu Said ibn Khamis al-Hilali bi-yadihi."
At the head of folio 10b: An ownership statement: "Ala hadha al-kitab al-mubarak bi-al-shira al-sahih min Suq al-Sughra bi-Nazwa li-Abd Allah ibn Masud ibn Rabiah al-Kindi."
On folio 99a: An ownership statement: "Ala hadha al-kitab ala khalaf al-Shaykh Amir ibn Said. Wa-inni al-aqall lillah Aqil (?) ibn Murbih (?) al-Mundhuri."

Colophon of Section 1: "Tamma naskh hadha al-juz duha al-Jumah, wa-thamaniyah wa-ishrin min shahr Dhi al-Qadah, sanat sitt sinin wa-arbain sanah bada alf sanah min Hijrat al-Nabi [23 April 1637], salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam. Naskhahu Khalaf ibn Muhammad ibn Khalaf al-Kindi al-Nazwi thumma al-Nahli, ghafara Allah la-hu wa-li-walidayhi wa-li-jami al-Muslimin wa-al-Muslimat, al-ahya minhum wa-al-amwat. Nasakhahu li-nafsihi. Wa-salla Allah ala Sayyidina Muhammad al-Nabi, wa-alihi wa-sallam. Wa-la hawla wa-la quwata illa billah al-Ali al-Azim al-Azim."

Colophon of Section 2: No colophon. Text ends abruptly, as follows: "... fa-li-tajal tuhraha ashrat ayyam wa-haydaha khamsat ashar yawman, fa-tumsiku min al-khamsat ashar al-yawm al-hayd an al-sawm wa-an al-salah ashrat ayyam, wa-tusalli khamsat ashar yawman wa-tasum. Fa-idha qadat al-sawm ala dhalika wa-aradat al-badal badal al-ashr allati kanat tahsabuha haydan alhaqat maaha badal khamsat ayyam hatta tatimma khamst ashar yawman, fa-takunu dhalika istihadah minha. Wa-amma in itaddat fa-anaha hadha jaalat haydaha khamsat ashar yawman wa-al-tuhr shahran. Qala wa-idha arafat waqt ummiha fa-huwa laha, wa-bi-hi takhudhu fi al-iddah al-salah wa-al-sawm ..."

Colophon of Section 3: No colophon. Text ends abruptly, as follows: "... Qultu kayfa nasnau. Fa-ala ma wasfta, fa-alladhi arafna fi dhalika annaha idha mudda biha al-dam bada ayyam haydiha, wa-kana dhalika al-dam sailan aw qatiran aw faidan muttasilan biha intazarat yawman aw yawmayn, mukhayyarah fi dhalika, taqudu fi intizariha inda al-salah wa-al-sawm. Fa-inn mudda biha al-dam fawqa al-yawm aw al-yawmayn fa-qad qala man qala inna alayha badal ..." Followed by three blank leaves.

title: 880-02 Nadrat al-ighrid fi nusrat al-qarid : manuscript / al-Muzaffar ibn al-Fadl al-Husayni.

notes.text: Title from folio 2b "... wa-qad wasamna hadha al-kitab bi-'Nadrat al-ighrid fi nusrat al-qarid' ..."

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. al-Hamdu lillah al-bahirah ayatuhu, al-qahirah satawatuhu, al-qadim ihsanuhu, al-azim sultanuhu, al-sabighah mawahibuhu, al-saighah masharibuhu, al-wasi juduhu, al-qami waiduhu ..."
Script: In medium clear naskh script; in black ink, on white polished paper; some notes and corrections on the margins; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and markings in red; text within red line border.
Binding: In dark brown leather, Type III (without flap); cover embossed with central medallion.

On folio 1a (in red): "Kitab 'Nadrat al-ighrid fi nusrat al-qarid', talif al-abd al-mushfiq min dhanbih, al-raji rahmat Rabbihi, Abi Ali al-Muzaffar ibn al-Sayyid Abi al-Qasim al-Fadl ibn Abi Jafar Yahya ibn Abi Yahya Abd Allah ibn Abi Abd Allah Jafar al-Alawi al-Husayni, ufiya anhu. Amin."
On folio 1a: An ownership statement: "Mimma intazama fi silk milk al-faqir ilayhi taala Ahmad ibn Nasir al-Din ibn Ali Biqai Zadah al-Shami, min khatt yadihi, ufiya anhum. Amin."
On folio 1a: An endowment statement: "Waqf"; An illegible endowment stamp; two illegible round stamps; and large round ownership stamp "Min mutamallakat al-faqir al-Hajj Mustafa Sidqi ghufira la-hu".

Colophon (folio 131b): "Katibuhu al-mustamidd min bahr karamihi taala wa-ihsanih, wa-al-laidh bi-atabih, wa-al-mustafid min ali jinabih, Ahmad ibn Nasir al-Din ibn Ali Biqai al-Shami, bi-Madinat Qustantiniyah, li-thaman layalin baqina min shahr Dhi al-Qadah, al-munsalikh min libas sanat tis wa-thalathin wa-miah wa-alf [11 July 1727], amaddahum Allah bi-al-afw wa-al-ghufran, maa al-mukhlisin min al-ikhwan. Amin, Amin. Wa-salla Allah ala Sayyidina Muhammad, wa-ala alihi wa-sahbihi wa-sallam. M."

On folios 132b-134a: A poem in 65 verses, by Kiwan Zadah Ahmad Bik Afandi al-Sharji (could not be identified). Starts with: Aarju min al-ilmami bi-al-talali al-bali // li-ma biya iblalan wa-dhalika abla li ..." And ends with: "Ahabbu ila qalbi min al-khuldi mawtinan // idha hawalu fi al-khuldi dhillata amthali." With the following note (in another hand): "Qad intahat hadhihi al-qasidah al-gharra al-mushtamilah ala al-fasahah wa-al-balaghah wa-insijam al-alfaz maa husn al-siyaghah bi-khatt yad munshiiha wa-nazimiha wa-amir riyadiha bi-badi naghamat hamaimiha akhina al-karim wa-sadiqina al-hamim al-bari al-fadil wa-al-lawdhai al-kamil Kiwan Zadah Ahmad Bik Afandi al-Sharji, harasa Allah dhatahu haythu kana, wa-abqahu bi-khayr wa-ihsan, bi-jah al-Nabi, alayhi al-salah wa-al-salam."
On folio 139a-139b: Miscellaneous anecdotes in prose and poetry.
On folio 139b: An ownership statement: "Min mutamallakat Ahmad Biqai Zadah, min khattihi, ufiya anhu."

title: 880-03 Kitab al-Diya : manuscript / Abu al-Mundhir Salamah ibn Muslim ibn Ibrahim al-Umani al-Awtabi al-Suhari .

notes.text: Copied on Friday, twelve nights having passed from the month of Muharram of the year 1127 of the Hijrah (18 January 1715), by Mahbub ibn Muhammad ibn Abd Allah ibn Said ibn Rashid al-Miwali, during the reign of al-Imam Sultan ibn Sayf ibn al-Imam Sultan ibn Sayf al-Yarubi, for al-Shaykh Ahmad ibn Sulayman ibn Ahmad al-Ati al-Manahi. Place of copying not mentioned.

Incipit (folio 10b): "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim, wa-bi-hi thiqati. al-Hamdu lillah alladhi la tudrikuhu al-ayun muawjudan, wa-la tasifuhu al-alsun mahdudan, wa-la yukayyifuhu al-fikr madudan, wa-la tarifuhu al-khaliqah walidan wa-la mawludan, ahmaduhu ala niamihi wa-alaih, wa-ashkuruhu ala husn qisamihi wa-balaihi, wa-audhu bi-hi min niqamihi wa-ibtilaihi, hamdan ithra hamd, wa-awdan bada buduwin ..."
Script: In fair large naskh script; in black ink, on white polished paper; some notes and corrections on the margins; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and markings in red.
Binding: In dark brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.

Inside the front cover: An ownership statement: "Hadha al-kitab mulkan li, wa-ana Muhammad ibn Jumah ibn Amir ibn Salih al-Ati, wa-katabtuhu bi-yadi." And a reader's statement: "Badana bi-qiraat hadha al-kitab yawm 13 Ramadan, sanat 1249 [24 January 1834]. Katabahu Said ibn Salim bi-yadihi."

On folio 6b-7a: A poem attributed to the author, starts as follows: "Wa-qala Abu al-Mundhir Salamah ibn Muslim ibn Ibrahim al-Umani al-Awtabi al-Suhari: Hadha kitabu diyain fi al-qulubi akhi // akrim bima fihi min ilmin wa-min adabi. Sammaytuhu bi-al-Diya idh kana fihi hudan // min al-ama wa-diya min zulmati al-atabi. Khasastu nafsi bi-hi hubban wa-marifatan // la-hu wa-sannaftuhu min asdaqi al-kutubi ..." And ends with: "... Hamaniya Allahu min zayghin wa-min zalalin // umri wa-allamani ilman wa-allama bi. Tammat al-abyat al-mansubah ila Abi al-Mundhir Salamah ibn Muslim al-Awtabi al-Suhari, taghammadahu Allah bi-rahmatihi."

On folio 7b: "al-Juz al-awwal. Fi talab al-ilm, min Kitab al-Diya, talif al-Shaykh al-Alim al-allamah, al-wari al-habr al-fahhamah, Abi al-Mundhir Salamah ibn Muslim ibn Ibrahim al-Umani al-Awtabi al-Suhari, taghammadahu Allah bi-rahmatihi. Wa-yatluhhu, in shaa Allah, al-juz al-thani min Kitab al-Diya, fima yajuzu min al-sifat, talif al-Shaykh Abi al-Mundhir Salamah ibn Muslim ibn Ibrahim al-Umani."
On folio 8b-9a: Table of contents (in 28 chapters)

Colophon (folio 261): "Tammat al-qitah al-ula min Kitab al-Diya, fi talab al-ilm wa-fi shay min al-tawhid, bi-awn Allah wa-hamdih, wa-salawatuhu ala Muhammad khayr khalqih wa-alihi wa-sallam. Wa-kana al-faragh min naskhihi sabah al-Jumah al-zahra, saat al-Qamar, li-ithnatay ashrata laylatin khalat min shahr Muharram al-haram, sanat sab sinin wa-ishrin wa-miah wa-alf sanah min al-Hijrah al-Nabawiyah [18 January 1715]. Wa-salla Allah ala Sayyidina Muhammad al-Nabi wa-alihi wa-sahbihi wa-sallama tasliman kathiran. Ala yaday al-abd al-aqall al-faqir lillah azza wa-jall, Mahbub ibn Muhammad ibn Abd Allah ibn Said ibn Rashid al-Miwali, fi asr al-Imam al-adl Sultan ibn Sayf ibn al-Imam Sultan ibn Sayf al-Yarubi, aazzahu Allah wa-nasarahu, lil-Shaykh al-Wali al-wali al-muwali, al-adl al-radi, Ahmad ibn Sulayman ibn Ahmad al-Ati al-Manahi, razaqahu Allah hifzahu wa-al-amal bi-ma fihi."

On the right margin of the colophon: "Urida ala nuskhatihi allati nusikha minha bi-hasb al-taqah wa-al-imkan bi-Hisn Qaryat Izki. Katabahu malikuhu min fadl malikihi, Ahmad ibn Sulayman ibn Ahmad al-Ati al-Manahi bi-yadihi, 14 Rabi al-Awwal, sanat 1127 [20 March 1715]."
On folio 262b: A poem (in 12 verses) by al-Muqanna al-Kindi (Muhammad ibn Umayrah, -approximately 690).
On folio 264b: A poem (in 9 verses) by Khalaf ibn Sinan.

title: 880-03 Fath al-aqfal wa-hall al-ishkal bi-Sharh Lamiyat al-afal : al-mashhur bi-al-Sharh al-kabir : manuscript / Jamal al-Din Muhammad ibn Umar Bahraq.

notes.text: Copied 15 Rabi al-Akhir, of the year 1021 of the Hijrah (15 June 1612), by Sultan ibn al-Imam Sayf ibn Sultan. Place of copying not mentioned.

Incipit (folio 3b): "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim, wa-bi-hi nastain, wa-alayhi natawakkalu, wa-Huwa hasbi wa-nima al-wakil. al-Hamdu lillah al-mutasarrif qabla ilal al-tasrif, al-mutaarrif qabla alat al-tarif, alladhi allafa al-ashya ahsana talif, wa-hammala al-insan amanat al-taklif, wa-sharrafa al-ilm wa-ahlahu akmal al-tashrif, ahmaduhu ala jami niamihi wa-afdalih, hamdan yaliqu bi-karam wajhihi wa-izz jalalih ..."
Script: In fair medium naskh script; in black ink, on thick white paper; some notes on the margins; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and markings in red; the verses of "Lamiyat al-afal" in bold script.
Binding: In dark brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.

On folio 1a: Two ownership statements: 1. "Hadha al-kitab illi lil-walad Hamid bi-al-irth min abihi." 2. "Hadha al-kitab illi li min mirath walidi Nasir ibn Ahmad al-Lamaki, wa-katabahu Ahmad ibn Nasir al-Lamaki bi-yadihi."

On folio 1b: An advice, by a reader/owner: "Haka nushi in kunta targhabu fihi, wa-maqali in kunta mimman yaihi, la takun labisan wa-anta haqir thawba kibarin wa-sahiban dhaylahu. Tamma hadha al-ithbat (?) bi-awn al-Malik al-Jabbar. Wa-katabahu Ahmad ibn Nasir bi-yadihi."

Colophon (folio 110b): "Tamma al-kitab bi-awn Allah taala, fi al-yawm al-khamis ashar min shahr Rabi al-Akhir, sanat 1021 min al-Hijrah al-Nabawiyah [15 June 1612], bi-qalam al-faqir ila Allah Sultan ibn al-Imam Sayf ibn Sultan, bi-yadihi. Nasakhahu li-waladihi wa-arin al-thiqah Nasir ibn Ahmad ibn Tamim ibn Ahmad al-Rustaqi, razaqahu Allah hifzahu wa-al-amal bima fihi. Wa-la hawla wa-la quwata illa billah al-Ali al-Azim."

On the right margin of the colophon: Partially obliterated ownership statement: "Hadha al-kitab lil-Shaykh al-thiqah [... ... ...]. Wa-katabahu al-abd al-faqir ila Allah [... ...] li-yalam al-waqif alayhi man malikuhu (?)."
On folio 111a: An unidentified text on morphology, titled "Nubdhah fi al-tasrif", by Sultan ibn al-Imam Sayf ibn Sultan ibn Sayf ibn Sultan ibn Sayf ibn Malik.
On folio 111b: An invocation (in crude script).

On folios 113a-116b (in a different hand): An unidentified long poem on "Tafsir al-ruya" (Interpretation of dreams). It starts with: al-Hamdu lillahi bari al-khalqi wa-al-suwari // wa-basiti al-rizqi lil-anami wa-al-bashari. Wa-kull khalqin barahu Allahu raziquhu // wa-Huwa al-ghaniyu ilahun ghayru muftaqiri. Wa-huwa al-Qadim wa-kullu al-khalqi ahdathahu // bi-la mithalin wa-lakin filu muqtadiri ..." It ends with: "... Abyatuha miatun maa tisatin adadan // wa-sittatun badaha jaat ala al-athari. Hadha wa-salla ilahu al-alamin ala // Muhammadin khayri mabuthin ala al-bashari. Wa-alihi al-ghurri wa-al-athari innahumu // khayru al-bariyati min badwin wa-min hadari."

On folio 119b: 1. Scribbles. 2. A borrowing note of the book: "Akhadhtu hadha al-kitab bi-al-ariyah al-mardudah ila ahliha, wa-huwa min ind al-akh Hamid ibn Muhammad ibn Tamim. Wa-katabahu afqar al-ibad al-aqall lillah abduhu Hamad ibn Nasir ibn Sulayman ibn Walid bi-yadihi. Tarikh nahar 16 min shahr Ramadan, sanat 1239 [15 May 1824]." 3. Two unidentified verses of poetry: "Idha lam takun ardi li-irdi masunatun // rahaltu wa-law nadat fa-lastu ujibuha. Rahaltu ila darin siwaha tuuzzuni // wa-law kana yawi li min al-jui dhibuha."

title: 880-03 Kitab Shamail al-Nabi salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam wa-akhlaquhu wa-afaluhu : manuscript / tasnif al-Shaykh al-Imam Abi Isa al-Tirmidhi.

notes.text: Copied on a Friday morning (day and month not mentioned), of the year 1253 of the Hijrah (1837 or 1838), in the city of Zabid (Yemen), by Muhammad Yasin al-Habashi.

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim, wa-bi-hi nastain. al-Hamdu lillah wa-salamun ala ibadihi alladhin istafa. Qala al-Shaykh al-Hafiz Abu Isa Muhammad ibn Isa ibn Surah al-Tirmidhi, rahimahu Allah taala: Bab ma jaa fi khalq Rasul Allah, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam, akhbarana Abu Raja Qutaybah ibn Sad, an Malik ibn Anas, an Rabiah ibn Abi Abd al-Rahman, an Anas ibn Malik, radiya Allah anhu, annahu samiahu yaqulu: Kana Rasul Allah, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam, laysa bi-al-tawil al-bain wa-la bi-al-qasir al-mutaraddid, wa-la bi-al-abyad al-amhaq, wa-la bi-al-jaid al-qatit, wa-la bi-al-sibt, baathahu Allah taala ala ras arbain sanah, fa-aqama bi-Makkah ashr sinin, wa-bi-al-Madinah ashr sinin, fa-tawaffahu Allah taala ala ras sittin sanah ..."
Script: In coarse medium naskh script; in black ink, on white paper; some notes and corrections on the margins; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and keywords in red.
Binding: The four loose quires are in a dark brown leather cover, Type III (without flap).
With one other title: Kitab Kanz al-haqaiq fi Hadith Khayr al-Khalaiq, by Abd al-Rauf ibn Taj al-Arifin al-Munawi.
Penciled note on last (blank) page: "Purchased at Mocha. C.P. [i.e. C. Pickering] 1844".

Colophon: "Tammat bi-hamd Allah wa-husn tawfiqih, fa-li-Allah al-hamd ala dhalik. Bi-raqm al-faqir ila Allah Muhammad Yasin al-Habashi, ghafara Allah la-hu wa-li-walidayhi, wa-li-jami mashayikhihi, wa-li-jami al-Muslimin, wa-dhalika nahar al-Jumah, waqt al-duha, bi-Madinat Zabid al-mahmiyah. Wa-salla Allah ala Sayyidina Muhammad, wa-ala alihi wa-sahbihi wa-sallam. Sanat 1253 [1837/1838]."
On the back of the wrapping sheet: A delivery note: "Ila Madinat Zabid. Sullima bi-yad al-Shaykh Muhammad ibn Umar Yasin al-Jabarti fi bayt Sayyidi Muhammad ibn Abd al-Rahman ibn Sulayman."

title: 880-02 Kitab Kanz al-haqaiq fi Hadith Khayr al-Khalaiq : manuscript / Abd al-Rauf ibn Taj al-Arifin al-Munawi.

notes.text: The manuscript is incomplete. Name of copyist and place and date of copying not mentioned, probably from the 19th century.

On folio 1a: "Kitab Kanz al-haqaiq fi Hadith Khayr al-Khalaiq, talif al-Shaykh al-Imam alam al-aimmah al-alam, al-hafiz al-muhaqqiq al-mudaqqiq Abd al-Rauf al-Munawi, rahimahu Allah rahmat al-abrar, wa-askanahu jannat tajri min tahtiha al-anhar, bi-haqq Nabiyihi al-Mukhtar, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam."

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Rabbi yassir wa-tammim. Ya Karim. al-Hamdu lillah alladhi kasa ahl al-Hadith burd al-sharaf fi kull iqlim, wa-rafaa shanahum, wa-ala dhikrahum fi kull hadith wa-qadim, wa-haffahum min bayn jumlat al-shar bi-mazid al-tashrif wa-al-tazim ... Wa-bad, yaqulu al-abd al-faqir al-qaim ala qadam al-taqsir, Abd al-Rauf al-Munawi: Hadha kitabun ujab, man taammalahu dakhalat alayhi al-masarrah min kull bab, jamatu fihi ashrat alaf Hadith fi ashrat kararis, kull kurras alf Hadith, fi kull waraqah miah Hadith ... wa-rattabtuhu ala huruf al-mujam ..."
Script: In fair naskh script; in black ink, on white paper; some notes and corrections on the margins; some catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and keywords in red.
Binding: The nine loose quires are in a dark brown leather cover, Type III (without flap).
With one other title: Shamail al-Nabi wa-akhlaquhu wa-afaluhu, by Muhammad ibn Isa al-Tirmidhi.
Penciled note on last (blank) page: "Purchased at Mocha. C.P. [i.e., C. Pickering] 1844".

Colophon: No colophon. Text ends abruptly, as follows: "... Nawm al-alim ibadah wa-nafasuhu tasbih. Nawmun ala ilm khayr min salah ala jahl. Niyat al-mumin khayrun min amalih. Fasl al-Muhalla bi-al-: al-Naihah malunah min hin takhruju min baytiha hatta tarjaa ..."

title: 880-01 al-Tuaf al-alyah f al-khuab al-minbaryah : manuscript.

notes.text: Name of the author could not be identified. Name of the copyist and place and date of copying not mentioned, probably from the 19th century.

Incipit: "Bismillh al-Ramn al-Ram. al-amdu lillh alladh rafaa al-khuab al al al-manbir, wa-jaaltahum [wa-jaalahum] qudwatan lil-lamn al-afiy wa-al-akbir ... Amm bad, fa-qad saalan ba al-ikhwn an amala dwnan f al-khuab yashtamilu al adad shuhr al-sanah, fa-ajabtuhu li-sulihi, rjiyan min Allh al-thawb ... wa-sammaytuhu bi-'al-Tuaf al-alyah f al-khuab al-minbaryah' ..."
Script: In fair naskh script; in black ink, on white thick paper; few notes on the margins; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and keywords in red.
Binding: In brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.

Colophon: No colophon. Text ends as follows: "... Ja f al-adth, an al-Nab, all Allh alayhi wa-sallam, annahu qla: Faraa Allh alayya wa-al ummat laylata al-isr khamsn altan fa-lam azal urjiuhu wa-asaluhu al-takhff att jaalah khamsan f kull yawm wa-laylah, wa-qla hiya khamsun wa-hunna khamsn, l yubaddalu al-qawl ladayya wa-l yunsakhu Kitb. Tamma hdh al-dwn al-mubbrak bi-amd Allh wa-awnihi."

title: 880-03 al-Tabsirah wa-al-tadhkirah : manuscript / Abd al-Rahim ibn al-Husayn al-Iraqi.

notes.text: Name of copyist and place and date of copying not mentioned, probably from the 18th century.

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Rabbi Yassir. Yaqulu raji Rabbihi al-Muqtadiri // Abd al-Rahimi ibn al-Husayni al-Athari. Min badi hamdi Allahi dhi al-alai // ala imtinanin jalla an ihsai. Thumma salatin wa-salamin daimin // ala Nabiyi al-khayri dhi al-marahimi. Fa-hadhihi al-maqasidu al-muhimmah // tudihu min ilmi al-Hadithi rasmah. Nazamtuha 'tabsiratan' lil-mubtadi // 'tadhkiratan' lil-muntahi wa-al-musnidi. Lakhkhastu fiha Ibna al-Salahi ajmaah // wa-zidtuha ilman tarahu mawdiah ..."
Script: In fair naskh script; in black ink, on cream color paper; some notes and corrections on the margins; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and markings in red.
Binding: The loose leaves are housed in a pocket in a modern cover.

Colophon: The text ends as follows: "... Wa-kamulat bi-Taybata al-maymunah // fa-barazat min khidriha masunah. Fa-Rabbuna al-mahmudu wa-al-mashkuru // ilayhi minna tarjiu al-umuru. Wa-afdalu al-salati wa-al-salami // ala al-Nabiyi Sayyidi al-anam. Tammat bi-hamd Allah wa-awnihi wa-husni tawfiqihi. Wa-salla Allah ala Sayyidina Muhammad wa-alihi."

title: 880-02 Kitab Basirat al-ahkam : manuscript / Uthman ibn Abi Ubayd Allah al-Asamm.

notes.text: Copied on Sunday, nine nights having passed from the month of Ramadan, of the year 1159 of the Hijrah (25 September 1746), by Khalfan ibn Khalid ibn Khalfan ibn Mahdi ibn Said ibn Jabr (Khayr?) ibn Ali ibn Salitah (?) ibn Sulayman ibn Khutam al-Saidi nasaban wa-al-Ibadi madhhaban, copied for his patron al-Faqih al-Alim Bajad ibn Salim ibn Bajad ibn Salim al-Ghafiri. Place of copying not mentioned.

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Rabbi Yassir. Ya Karim. al-Hamdu lillah alladhi la ilaha illa Huwa, laysa ka-mithlihi shay, wa-Huwa al-sami [al-sami] al-basir, fa-nafsuhu dhatuhu, wa-dhatuhu ithbatuhu, wa-Huwa al-alim [al-alim] al-qadir, wa-salla Allah ala Rasulihi Muhammad al-Nabi, wa-ala alihi, wa-Huwa al-bashir al-nadhir, wa-sallama tasliman. Bab fi al-buyu wa-ma yajuzu minha wa-ma la yajuz ..."
Script: In fair naskh script; in black ink, on polished white paper; some notes and corrections on the margins; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and markings in red.
Binding: In dark brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.

Inside the front cover: "Min kitab al-musannif: Wa-idha tanazaa Ahl al-Dhimmah wa-al-Muslimun fi amwal kanat al-khusumah baynahum fi dhalika ka-al-khusumah wa-al-hukm bayna al-Muslimin. Wa-qala Muhammad ibn Mahbub qawlan yadullu ala ghayr hadha fi Dhimmi ishtara malan min Muslim, jaza an yukhadha minhu shafat al-Islam wa-in lam yakun jaran lil-mal, wa-kadhalika law wajaba ala maytin haqq li-Muslim wa-haqq li-Dhimmi annahu yadfau ila al-Dhimmi ma fadula min al-mal bada istifa al-Muslim haqqahu. Wa-Allah alam. Katabahu Said ibn Salim ibn Said bi-yadihi."

On folio 3a: An ownership statement: "Ishtaraytu hadha al-kitab min Suq al-Muslimin min Bandar Muskad min ind Haydar Jadid bi-thalath ashar Muhammadiyah bayad wa-kasr, wa-ana al-faqir lillah taala Ahmad ibn Hammad ibn Muhammad ibn Salim al-Bast, fi 11 Rajab, sanat 1260 [27 July 1844]."

On folio 3b-4b: Table of contents "Tartib al-abwab li-hadha al-kitab". At the end of the table of contents: "Tammat al-abwab bi-awn al-Malik al-Wahhab. Hadha al-kitab 'Basirat al-ahkam' talif al-Faqih al-ajall, al-alim al-afdal, Abi Muhammad Uthman ibn Abd Allah al-Asamm, rahimahu Allah. Wa-salla Allah ala Sayyidina Muhammad al-Nabi wa-sahbihi wa-sallam. Katabahu Abd Allah Bajad ibn Salim bi-yadihi. Badana tashih hadha al-kitab laylat al-Thulatha, 7 al-Hijjah, sanat 1159 [21 December 1746]."

Colophon (folio 106a): "Tamma al-kitab bi-awn Allah wa-husn tawfiqih, wa-al-salah wa-al-salam ala khayr khalqih, Muhammad, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam. Wa-kana tamamuhu fi yawm al-Ahad, li-tis layalin khalawna min shahr Ramadan al-sharif, alladhi huwa min shuhur sanat 1159 [25 September 1746] min al-Hijrah al-Islamiyah, ala muhajiriha afdal al-salah wa-al-salam, ala yad al-abd al-aqall lillah azza wa-jall, Khalfan ibn Khalid ibn Khalfan ibn Mahdi ibn Said ibn Jabr (?) ibn Ali ibn Salitah (?) ibn Sulayman ibn Khutam al-Saidi nasaban wa-al-Ibadi madhhaban, nasakhahu li-Sayyidihi wa-Waliyihi al-Faqih al-Alim Bajad ibn Salim ibn Bajad ibn Salim al-Ghafiri, razaqahu Allah hifzahu wa-al-amal bima fihi, innahu wali dhalika wa-al-qadir alayhi. Wa-la hawla wa-la quwata illa billah al-Ali al-Azim. Wa-salla Allah ala Rasulihi Muhammad al-Nabi, wa-alihi wa-sahbihi, wa-sallam. Amin."

Under the colophon: Collation statement: "Urida ala nuskhatihi allati nusikha minha ala hasb al-taqah wa-al-makan [wa-al-imkan], wa-Allah alam bi-sihhatihi, wa-kana tamam dhalika laylat al-Arbia, 1 al-Hijjah, sanat 1159 [15 December 1746]."
On folio 106b-107a: Miscellaneous "fatwas" (legal opinions) by several Islamic law scholars.

title: 880-02 Kitab al-Tartib : manuscript / Yusuf ibn Ibrahim al-Warjalani.

notes.text: Copied on Thursday, 7 Muharram, of the year 1114 of the Hijrah (3 June 1702), by Mubarak ibn Rashid ibn Makram ibn Rashid al-Makrami al-Rustaqi, during the reign of Sayf ibn Sultan ibn Sayf ibn Malik ibn Abi al-Arab al-Yarubi. Place of copying "Baldatata (baldatina (?) min al-Sanad (al-Sind)" could not be identified.

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. al-Juz al-awwal min 'Kitab al-Tartib', mimma rattabahu al-Shaykh al-awhad, al-rais al-amjad al-afdal, Abu Yaqub Yusuf ibn Abi Ibrahim ibn Munadi al-Sidarati al-Ibadi, radiya Allah anhu, wa-salla Allah ala Rasulihi Muhammad al-Nabi, wa-alihi wa-sallam. Bab fi al-niyah: Qala Abu Amr al-Rabi ibn Habib ibn Amr al-Basri: Haddathani Abu Ubaydah Muslim ibn Abi Karimah al-Tamimi an Jabir ibn Zayd al-Azdi an Abd Allah ibn Abbas an al-Nabi, salla Allah alayh wa-sallam 'Niyatu al-mumin khayrun min amalih' ..."
Script: In fair naskh script; in black ink, on cream color paper; some notes and corrections on the margins; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and markings in red.
Binding: In brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with gilded central medallion and frame.

Inside the front cover: An ownership statement: "Hadha al-kitab al-musamma al-Tartib malakahu [...] Ahmad ibn Hammad ibn Muhammad ibn Salim ibn Khamis [...] ibn Khalid ibn Hasan ibn Ibrahim [...] ibn Ahmad ibn Abd Allah al-Basat [...]. Katabahu bi-yadihi yawm 23 Jumada al-Ula, sanat 1253 [25 August 1837], wa-ala Allah al-tawakkul (?) [...]. Hadha al-kitab Naam huwa li-Ahmad [...]. Katabahu Sulayman ibn Salim [...]."
On preliminary leaf 1a: Two black square stamps (partially legible).

Colophon (folio 237b-238a): "Tamma al-juz al-rabi min Kitab al-Tartib min al-sahih fi Hadith Rasul Allah, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam. Wa-kana al-faragh min naskhihi nahar al-Khamis, tarikh sabi min shahr al-Muharram, min shuhur sanat arba ashrah sanah wa-miat sanah wa-alf sanah [3 June 1702], min Hijrat al-Nabi Muhammad, alayhi afdal al-salah wa-al-salam. Wa-kana tamamuhu (naskhuhu) fi Baldatata [baldatina (?)] min al-Sanad [al-Sind(?)], wa-dhalika fi asr Sayyidina wa-Mawlana, Imam al-Muslimin, Sayf ibn Sultan ibn Sayf ibn Malik ibn Abi al-Arab al-Yarubi, nasarahu Allah ala jami adaihi. Wa-katibuhu al-faqir lillah taala, al-aqall, khadim al-Imam al-muqaddam dhikruhu, al-faqir Mubarak ibn Rashid ibn Makram ibn Rashid al-Makrami al-Rustaqi. Asalu Allah an yarzuqani al-amal bi-ma fihi wa-yatajawaza anni, innahu ghafurun rahim."

On folio 238b: An ownership statement: "Hadha al-kitab <ila> li-Abd Allah ibn Hamad ibn Said (?) ibn Thani (?) bi-al-shira min ind Rashid ibn Muhammad ibn Rashid ibn Khasib al-Riyai (?) al-Bahlawi al-Riyai yaskunu al-Ghaf wa-al-dallal (?) Salimin ibn Abd Allah ibn Said (?) ibn Muqni al-Saali al-Nazwi, yawm 15 Shaban, sanat 34 (1134) [31 May 1722], fi asr al-Imam Sayf ibn Sultan ibn Sayf ibn Sultan ibn Sayf ibn Malik al-Yarubi, aazzahu Allah wa-nasarahu, fi awwal Mulkihi aqib al-Imam Yarub."

title: Principles of faith in Islam : manuscript.

notes.text: Name of author/copyist, and place of authorship/copying not mentioned.
A note on folio 1a: "Purchased at Zanzibar, Sept. 2d, 1844. C.P. [i.e., C. Pickering]."
A note on the right margin of folio 2a is dated "Sanat 1120" (Year 1708/1709).

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. al-Hamdu lillah Rabb al-Alamin wa-al-afiyah lil-muttaqin. Wa-al-salah wa-al-salam ala Rasul Allah, Sayyidina Muhammad, al-Nabbi al-Ummi, wa-ala alihi wa-sahbihi wa-sallam, ajmain. Wa-bad, fa-yajibu ala al-abd awwala an yarifa al-iman wa-al-Islam. Fa-in qila laka ma awwal shay yajibu ala al-insan, fa-qul ala kull mukallaf an yarifa annahu makhluq, wa-anna la-hu khaliqan wa-raziqan wa-huwa Allah alladhi la ilaha illa huwa, thumma yajibu alayhi an yarifa al-iman wa-al-Islam, li-anna saadat [al-]darayn la yakunu illa bihima ..."
Script: In fair naskh script; in black ink, on thick cream color paper; text fully vocalized; catchwords.
Binding: Unbound. The eight leaves (one quire) are housed in a dark brown folded sheet of parchment.

Colophon: No colophon. Text ends as follows: "... wa-amma alladhin lam yasjud wa-lam yandam hum alladhin yuladun kafiran wa-yamutuna kafiran. Allahumma la tajalna minhum, fa-hum sabab sara al-nas arbaat al-tawaif. Allahumma ijalna wa-iyakum min alladhin al-taifah alladhin yuladuna Muslimin wa-yamutuna Muslimin, bi-barakat Nabiyina Muhammad, salla Allah alayhi wa-sallam, wa-ala alihi wa-sahbihi ajmain, wa-ijalna min al-tabiin lahum qawlan wa-filan. Amin. Tamma al-kitab."

title: 880-03 Durrat al-ghawwas fi awham al-khawass : manuscript / Abu Muhammad al-Qasim ibn Ali ibn Muhammad ibn Uthman al-Hariri al-Basri.

notes.text: Copied on Friday, 23 Muharram, of the year 1195 of the Hijrah (19 January 1781), by Umar ibn Sulayman. Place of copying not mentioned.

Incipit: "Bismillah al-Rahman al-Rahim. Qala al-Shaykh al-Rais Abu Muhammad al-Qasim ibn Ali ibn Muhammad ibn Uthman al-Hariri al-Basri, radiya Allah anhu: Bada hamd Allah alladhi amma ibadahu bi-wazaif al-awarif, wa-khassa man shaa minhum bi-lataif al-maarif, wa-al-salah ala Muhammad al-aqib, wa-ala alihi wa-ashabihi uli al-manaqib, fa-inni raytu kathiran mimman tasannamu asnimat al-rutab wa-tawassamu simatan qad dahaw al-ammah fi bad ma yafrutu min kalamihim ... wa-sammaytuhu 'Durrat al-ghawwas fi awham al-khawass' ..."
Script: In good calligraphic naskh script; in black ink, on polished white paper; catchwords.
Decoration: Keywords and markings in red.
Binding: In dark brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with gilded central medallion.
Inside the front cover: "La din illa al-Islam, wa-la madhhab illa madhhab ahl al-istiqamah, ala wa-hum al-firqah al-Ibadiyah al-mardiyah."

On folio 1a: Two popular medicinal recipes, and two ownership statements: 1. "Hadha al-kitab li, wa-huwa fi milki, wa-ana al-haqir Ahmad ibn Hammad ibn Muhammad ibn Salim al-Bast, hurrira bi-yadihi (?), 8 Safar, sanat 1260 [28 February 1844]." 2. "Hadha al-kitab, wa-huwa fi milki, wa-ana al-haqir Ahmad ibn Hammad ibn Muhammad ibn Salim al-Bast. Fi shahr Safar, hurrira fi yawm thamin, fi sanat 1260 [28 February 1844]. Wa-katabahu al-haqir Sad ibn Nasir ibn Abd al-Rasul."

Inside the back cover: "Tarikh yawm safar ila Bandar Zanjibar yawm 8 Muharram, sanat 1260 [29 January 1844], wa-kana Khalaf (?) ibn Salim ibn Khalaf (?) ibn Salim al-Bast. Wasaltu Bandar Maskad hal rujuina yawm 24 Rabi al-Awwal, sanat 1260 [13 April 1844]."

Colophon (flolio 119b): "Tammat hadhihi al-nuskhah al-sharifah nahar al-Jumah, al-thalith wa-al-ishrin min Muharram al-haram, sanat 1195 [19 January 1781], bi-yad al-haqir Umar ibn Sulayman, ghafara Allah la-hu wa-li-walidayhi, wa-ahsana ilayhima wa-ilayhi."

title: 880-03 Dalil al-khayrt wa-shawriq al-anwr f dhikr al-alh al al-Nab al-Mukhtr : manuscript / Muammad ibn Sulaymn al-Jazl.

notes.text: Name of copyist and place and date of copying not mentioned, probably from the eighteenth century.

Incipit: "Bismillh al-Ramn al-Ram. Wa-all Allh al Sayyidin Muammad, wa-al lihi wa-abihi wa-sallam. al-amdu lillh alladh hadn lil-mn wa-al-islm, wa-al-alh al Muammad Nabyihi alladh istanqadhan bi-hi min ibdat al-awthn wa-al-anm, wa-al lihi wa-abihi al-nujab al-bararah al-kirm. Wa-bad hdh, fa-al-ghara f hdh al-kitb dhikr al-alh al al-Nab, all Allh alayhi wa-sallam, wa-failih, nadhkuruh madhfat al-asnd li-yashula ifuh al al-qri, wa-hiya min ahamma al-muhimmt li-man yurdu al-qurb min Rabb al-Arbb. Wa-sammaytuhu bi-kitb "Dalil al-khayrt wa-shawriq al-anwr f dhikr al-alh al al-Nab al-Mukhtr" ibitghan li-mart Allh tal wa-maabbatan f Raslihi al-Karm ..."
Secundo folio: dhikr al-alh al al-Nab, all Allh alayhi wa-sallam wa-failih.
12.5 x 19.5 cm; written surface: 7 x 13 cm; 11 lines per page.
Binding: In brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover and flap embossed with central medallion.
Script: In good naskh script, in black ink, on thin cream color paper; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings in red; markings in red and gold; text fully vocalized and framed in gold; at the head of folio 1b a design colored in green, red, blue, gold, etc.
Some notes on the margins (in Arabic, Ottoman Turkish, and Persian);

Colophon: No colophon. The text of "Dalil al-khayrt" ends on folio 75a with an invocation, as follows: "... Wa-nasaluka Allhumma bi-nr wajhika alladh malaa arkn arshika an tazraa f qalb marifatika att arifaka aqqa marifatika, kam yanbagh an turafa bi-hi. Wa-all Allh al Sayyidin Muammad khtim al-nabyin wa-imm al-mursaln, wa-al lihi wa-abihi wa-sallama taslman. Wa-al-amdu lillh Rabb al-lamn, wa-Huwa asb wa-nima al-wakl. Wa-l awla wa-l qwata ill billh al-Al al-Am."

title: Stephen Vincent Benet letter, to Major Pond, 1928 September : manuscript.

notes.text: This letter is addressed to Major Pond, but Benet may have forgotten, or was unaware, that Major James B. Pond had passed away in 1903. James Barton Pond, Jr. ran his father's lecture managment company after his father's death, and this may be who Benet was intending to address in this letter.
Accompanied by a typescript transcription of the letter with pencil revisions in an unknown hand.
Date is taken from a answered stamp on the letter, dated September 17, 1928, indicating that Pond had answered Benet's letter on that date.

title: Rudyard Kipling letter, to Bernard Spring Rice, 1926 June 16 : manuscript.
The Absent minded beggar : manuscript / Rudyard Kipling.

notes.text: Script: In fine calligraphic naskh script; in black ink, on white paper; catchwords.
Decoration: Text within colored line border; splended unwans in the beginning and at end.
Binding: In dark brown leather, Type II (with flap); cover embossed with gilded central medallion and frame. Binding deteriorated.
Name of authors /copyists, and place of authorship/copying not mentioned, probably from the 18th century.
Script: In fair West African Arabic script; in black ink, on mostly thick cream color paper; some texts fully vocalized; some catchwords.
Layout: Single column of different lines.
Binding: In separate leaflets housed between two separate covers of brown leather.
Script: In fair naskh script; in black and red ink, on paper; some notes and corrections on the margins; some catchwords.
Layout: Single column of different lines.
Binding: In dark brown leather cover, Type II (with flap); cover embossed with central medallion; cover deteriorated.
Former call number distinguishes RL 177 I, RL 177 II, and RL 177 III. These three units are housed together under call number RL 177.
Script: In serto (West Syriac script), in different hands; in black ink, on thick cream color paper; few notes on the margins; catchwords.
Decoration: Headings and markings in red.
Layout: In single and double column of different lines.

On the page attached to folio 1: "This ancient Ms. I obtained from a Jacobite in Mosul and may serve to show those who read Gershuni (Arabic in Syriac characters) the mode of interpreting the mooted passages in the N. T. on which are formulated the tenets of the Jacobite Monophysites of Mesopotamia. It is entitled The Book of Questions. The answers, it is but just to say, are not generally accepted by this sect at present. A small gift to the American Oriental Society, New Haven, CT."
On folio 1a: Two ownership statements: "1. [Hadh]a mal Abd Allah ibn Abd al-Karim alladhi (?) huwa min Balad [...] al-mamurah." 2. "Hadha mal Abd al-Masih."

On folio 5a: An index of "Kitab al-tilmidh wa-al-muallim" (in 22 chapters), copied by Istanis: "Kamulat fahrasat Kitab al-mubarak al-azim Kitab al-tilmidh wa-al-muallim." And in Syriac: "Usalaw bhuba Alahaya al al Estanis mhila da-ktab."
On folio 122a and 122b: An ownership statement: "Hadha al-kitab mal Hajar (?) ibn Antun."
At the end of folio 125b: "Kamula wa-najaz 'Kitab al-Maqalat' bi-awn Allah, ala yad ahqar abid Allah, Mansur al-dhalil al-haqir al-gharib al-mustaghfir, wa-lillah al-majd."

At the end of folio 133a: "Kamula bi-awn Allah Qissat Rahib al-Sin, ajal al-rahib al-mukarram, al-rajul al-fazil, Rahib Ishu, salatuhu maana. Amin. Wa-ana al-khati atlubu al-maghfirah min al-nazir fi hadhihi al-qissah, wa-kull man qaraa wa-kataba wa-qala Amin. Amin."
At the end of folio 152b: "Kamula bi-awn Allah 'Suud al-Qiddis Bulus', salatuhu maana. Amin."
On the right margin of folio 160b: Some calculations and an illegible stamp.
On the margins of folio 161a: Some calculations and scribbles.
At the end of folio 163b: "Kamulat Masail Basiliyus wa-Gharighuriyus, wa-al-hamdu lillah Rabb al-Alamin. Amin. Amin. Amin. Wa-rahmat Allah ala Mansur al-miskin. Srit ba-shnat APPA (?) d-Yawn."
At the end of folio 193b: "Kamulat Qissat Mar Gharighuriyus bi-awn min Allah."
At the end of folio 196b: "Kamulat Qissat al-Malik al-Ibn."
At the margins of folio 197a: Some scribbles and calculations."
At the end of folio 212a: "Kamula Iktishaf Shamun bi-awn Allah."
On folio 220a: A medicinal recipe and some calculations.

On folio 220b: An ownership statement: "Hadha al-kitab al-mubarak mal Jirjis ibn Antun qad kana waqaa fi sahmihi min hissat Asad Abd al-Aziz, Ma la-hu ahad dawah wa-la tilbah. Sanat [...] Masihiyah." And some scribbles.
On folio 255b. At the end of the Syriac treatise 'Teksa gawanaya': "Shlem b-idran Maran."
At the end of folio 232a: "Kamulat Risalat Anba Bisindah salatuhu maana. Amin."
Binding: In dark red leather, Type III (without flap).
Inside the back cover: "Yasal al-khatt ila mahrusat (mahrusat?) al-Musil wa-yatasallam bi-yad Qass Nimat Allah al-mukarram." And some scribbles.
Title from manuscript; title is written on verso of each leaf in the right margin in red ink.
Layout: single column of eight lines
Binding: unbound. Manuscript leaves have two holes for string intended to bind together leaves.
Decoration: decorated with stylized pipal leaves in red ink at both ends of each leaf (recto and verso).
Title from manuscript; title is written on verso of each leaf in the right margin in red ink.
Layout: single column of six lines
Script: tamarind-seed Burmese script; written in laquer on a gold background.
Binding: stored in red wooden covers. One hole for binding string can be seen on all the leaves and covers. String itself is wanting.

Decoration: decorated margins on first and final leaves depicting devas holding flower. The front and back covers are highly decorated and depict two pairs of devas facing each other, and surrounding motifs include intertwined nagas,foliage, and birds.

The pagination markers (in circles on the left of each leaf) seem to have been supplied by a later hand, replacing earlier ones that had become faint. After the first leaf, the pagination system changes (ka, kha, khi, khi... rather than e.g. ka, ka, ki, ki...).
